    <p>Welcome to <a href="https://www.cs.cmu.edu/~cx/">Chenyan Xiong</a>âs research groupâs website. We are based in the <a href="https://lti.cmu.edu/">Language Technologies Institute</a> at Carnegie Mellon Universityâs School of Computer Science. Our work broadly spans areas in information retrieval, natural language processing, and machine learning. A few of our current research topics include (but are not limited to):</p>

<ul>
  <li>
<strong>Foundational models</strong>: data curation for pretraining, efficient language models, and interpretability.</li>
  <li>
<strong>Retrieval</strong>: dense retrieval, representations for universal information retrieval.</li>
  <li>
<strong>Applications</strong>: LLMs for healthcare, retrieval grounded in special domains (e.g., multimodal, long document).</li>
</ul>

<p><em>Update April 2024: Our website is up! Please check back in the following weeks for updates.</em></p>

